Azur Hires Lazard to Advise on Funding Options, Times Says

-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 
2011-05-22T11:06:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/azur-hires-lazard-to-advise-on-funding-options-times-says.html
Azur Pharma Ltd ., the closely held
pharmaceutical company, hired investment bank Lazard Ltd. to
advise on future funding options, including the sale of a stake
in the business, the  Sunday Times  reported, without citing
anyone.  The Dublin-based company, founded by former Elan Corp Plc
executive Seamus Mulligan, is worth more than $500 million, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Brennan in Dublin at 
 jbrennan29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  